WEBVTT

00:03.500 --> 00:04.166
I KNOW WHO YOU ARE.

00:04.166 --> 00:05.875
YOU ONLY JUST MET ME.

00:05.875 --> 00:07.500
I KNOW YOU'RE A SNAKE
AND A CON ARTIST.

00:07.500 --> 00:08.750
I KNOW YOU'VE
SLEPT YOUR WAY

00:08.750 --> 00:10.208
THROUGH THE
FEMALE STUDENT BODY

00:10.208 --> 00:11.500
AND HALF THE FACULTY.

00:11.500 --> 00:13.166
THE KIND OF BOY
WHO'LL BREAK YOUR HEART

00:13.166 --> 00:15.041
AND THEN START IN
ON YOUR SISTER

00:17.375 --> 00:18.333
AHH.

00:18.333 --> 00:21.000
YOU MUST BE CONFUSED.
UNDERSTANDABLE.

00:21.000 --> 00:21.834
IT'S A COMMON AFFLICTION
AMONG BLONDES.

00:21.834 --> 00:24.750
UGH.
TRUTH IS,

00:24.750 --> 00:25.875
I'M NONE OF THOSE THINGS.

00:25.875 --> 00:27.667
OH, YEAH?

00:27.667 --> 00:29.333
THEN WHO ARE YOU?

00:29.333 --> 00:32.583
I'M JUST THE BOY THAT'S
GONNA TEAR YOUR SOUL APART.

00:35.333 --> 00:38.291
THIS IS RIDICULOUS.
I CAN'T DO THIS.

00:38.291 --> 00:40.250
AH, CUT. I GUESS.

00:40.250 --> 00:42.542
AMATEURS.
I'M SURROUNDED BY AMATEURS.

00:42.542 --> 00:44.417
WILL YOU JUST
RUN WITH ME HERE
FOR A SECOND.

00:44.417 --> 00:46.917
IF I WERE A GIRL
TRYING TO SEDUCE A BOY--

00:46.917 --> 00:49.250
AND TRUST ME, OK,
I'VE BEEN THAT GIRL
MANY TIMES--

00:49.250 --> 00:51.208
I WOULD NEVER
LET HIM KNOW
HOW MUCH I WANT HIM.

00:51.208 --> 00:52.458
NEVER. EVER. I MEAN,

00:52.458 --> 00:53.708
THAT'S THE MOMENT
WHEN THEY LOSE INTEREST.

00:53.708 --> 00:56.375
SORRY, IT'S JUST--
IT'S FEEBLE WRITING.

00:56.375 --> 00:59.250
HEY, HEY. I'M RIGHT HERE.

00:59.250 --> 01:01.708
WE SHOULD'VE MADE
AN ANIMATED MOVIE.

01:01.708 --> 01:02.959
WOULDA-COULDA-SHOULDA.

01:02.959 --> 01:04.041
HMM.

01:04.041 --> 01:07.083
ALL RIGHT.

01:07.083 --> 01:08.959
AUDREY...

01:10.708 --> 01:12.708
YOU GOTTA PENETRATE
THE SUBTEXT, OK?

01:12.708 --> 01:13.917
REMEMBER, SHE KNOWS
THAT HE KNOWS THAT SHE KNOWS

01:13.917 --> 01:15.041
WHAT KIND OF MAN HE IS.

01:15.041 --> 01:17.208
SO IF HE KNOWS
THAT SHE KNOWS

01:17.208 --> 01:18.667
AND SHE KNOWS
THAT HE KNOWS...

01:18.667 --> 01:20.083
SEE WHAT I'M GETTING AT?

01:20.083 --> 01:22.000
YEAH.
ALL RIGHT. GREAT.

01:22.000 --> 01:23.208
ALL RIGHT.
LET'S SHOOT THE SCENE

01:23.208 --> 01:25.542
BEFORE WE GET OLD
AND DIE IN OUR SLEEP.

01:27.625 --> 01:30.000
OK. BACK TO ONE, PEOPLE.

01:31.917 --> 01:34.750
OH, I'M SORRY.

01:34.750 --> 01:37.333
AH, PACE, IF YOU DON'T
SWING THE MICROPHONE,

01:37.333 --> 01:39.583
YOU RUN LESS OF A RISK
OF DIPPING INTO MY SHOT,

01:39.583 --> 01:42.750
WHICH, I THINK, WOULD
DETRACT FROM THE OVERALL
REALITY OF THE PICTURE.

01:42.750 --> 01:45.000
GOTCHA. IT'LL BE
PERFECT THIS TIME.

01:45.000 --> 01:47.375
ALL RIGHT. PICTURE'S UP.

01:55.083 --> 01:57.750
OK. WE ARE ROLLING.

01:57.750 --> 01:59.834
MARKER.

01:59.834 --> 02:02.417
27 APPLE, TAKE 3.

02:07.125 --> 02:09.583
AND...

02:09.583 --> 02:10.542
ACTION.

02:56.458 --> 02:58.792
REMEMBER,
THERE IS NO DISTINCTION

02:58.792 --> 03:01.083
BETWEEN WRITING A STORY
AND LIVING YOUR LIFE.

03:01.083 --> 03:03.667
THE SAME ELEMENTS THAT MAKE
A MOMENT IN YOUR LIFE

03:03.667 --> 03:06.500
IGNITE, EXPLODE, MOVE--
THESE SAME THINGS

03:06.500 --> 03:10.000
MAKE A SCENE
IN YOUR WRITING HAVE LIFE.

03:10.000 --> 03:11.417
WHEN A WRITER HAS
EVOLVED IN THEIR WORK,

03:11.417 --> 03:14.000
THEY'VE EVOLVED
AS AN INDIVIDUAL.

03:14.000 --> 03:15.083
WHEN THE WORK IS INTENSE,

03:15.083 --> 03:17.625
IT IS BECAUSE
THEIR LIFE IS INTENSE.

03:17.625 --> 03:18.375
SO THE REAL QUESTION IS,

03:18.375 --> 03:21.208
"WHAT MAKES LIFE INTENSE?"

03:21.208 --> 03:22.667
CONFLICT. WHAT IS CONFLICT?

03:22.667 --> 03:25.625
THE ESSENTIAL CONFLICT
AT THE CORE OF THE ARTIST?

03:25.625 --> 03:27.667
UH, THINK OF THE MOVIES
YOU'VE SEEN,

03:27.667 --> 03:29.417
SONGS YOU'VE HEARD,
BOOKS YOU'VE READ.

03:29.417 --> 03:31.667
"TO BE OR NOT TO BE."
BINGO.

03:31.667 --> 03:32.708
IN OTHER WORDS,

03:32.708 --> 03:34.125
YOUR DESIRES
VERSUS YOUR IDEALS.

03:34.125 --> 03:36.750
YOUR HEAD, OR YOUR HEART.

03:36.750 --> 03:38.208
CAN SOMEBODY
GIVE ME AN EXAMPLE,

03:38.208 --> 03:40.083
USING THEIR OWN LIFE,
OF A CONFLICT BETWEEN

03:40.083 --> 03:42.083
THEIR DESIRES
AND THEIR IDEALS?

03:43.208 --> 03:44.750
I HAVE AN EXAMPLE.

03:47.083 --> 03:47.875
OUT WITH IT THEN.

03:47.875 --> 03:51.041
WELL, IT'S UM...

03:51.041 --> 03:53.041
IT'S ABOUT A GUY.

03:53.041 --> 03:55.000
AH, OF COURSE.
ISN'T IT ALWAYS?

03:55.000 --> 03:57.625
[LAUGHS]

03:57.625 --> 03:58.375
[BELL RINGS]

03:58.375 --> 04:00.083
OH, THAT'S TOO BAD.

04:00.083 --> 04:01.792
I WAS CURIOUS WHERE
YOUR STORY WAS GOING.

04:01.792 --> 04:04.667
YOU'LL HAVE TO SHARE
WITH US NEXT WEEK.

04:04.667 --> 04:06.375
"SAME BAT TIME.
SAME BAT CHANNEL."

04:15.875 --> 04:17.083
WE NEED TO TALK.

04:17.083 --> 04:17.916
WE DO?

04:17.916 --> 04:19.583
YES. THAT WAS
UNCOMFORTABLE.

04:19.583 --> 04:20.166
NO, THAT WAS
CREATIVE WRITING.

04:20.166 --> 04:22.083
"UNCOMFORTABLE"

04:22.083 --> 04:23.500
IS TAUGHT DOWN THE
HALL ON THE LEFT.

04:23.500 --> 04:25.250
THERE SHOULD BE
A WORD FOR PEOPLE

04:25.250 --> 04:26.083
WHO USE SARCASM
AS A DEFENSE MECHANISM.

04:26.083 --> 04:27.834
THERE IS. SARCASTIC.

04:27.834 --> 04:30.208
I'M SERIOUS.

04:30.208 --> 04:31.417
ARE YOU OK?

04:31.417 --> 04:33.583
I'M FINE. I...

04:33.583 --> 04:35.750
I MEAN, I'D BE LYING
IF I SAID I WASN'T

04:35.750 --> 04:37.750
A LITTLE WEIRDED OUT
BY RECENT EVENTS.

04:37.750 --> 04:40.625
I'M SORRY, JOEY.
I'M A CREEP. I...

04:40.625 --> 04:42.750
I'VE ROBBED YOU OF YOUR
INNOCENCE, HAVEN'T I?

04:42.750 --> 04:45.000
NO, YOU'RE NOT A CREEP.

04:45.000 --> 04:46.500
AND DON'T SAY YOU'RE SORRY,

04:46.500 --> 04:47.583
IT MAKES ME FEEL--

04:47.583 --> 04:49.125
CHEAP?

04:49.125 --> 04:50.125
NO.

04:50.125 --> 04:51.250
DIRTY?
NO.

04:51.250 --> 04:52.667
OK, I'M GONNA
STOP TALKING,

04:52.667 --> 04:53.834
BECAUSE, OBVIOUSLY,

04:53.834 --> 04:55.667
THERE ARE SOME THINGS
YOU WANNA SAY TO ME.

04:55.667 --> 04:58.291
MANY THINGS.
OK...

04:58.291 --> 05:00.166
I CAN'T PROMISE I'LL
HAVE ALL THE ANSWERS.

05:00.166 --> 05:01.583
IN FACT, I CAN'T PROMISE
I'LL HAVE ANY ANSWERS,

05:01.583 --> 05:04.250
BUT I'M WILLING
TO GIVE IT A SHOT.

05:04.250 --> 05:07.750
THANK YOU.

05:07.750 --> 05:09.333
WHENEVER YOU'RE READY.

05:14.708 --> 05:16.458
YOU KNOW, IT'S KIND OF
A LOTTA PRESSURE,

05:16.458 --> 05:17.792
AND I SEEM TO BE
FREEZING UP,

05:17.792 --> 05:18.959
SO CAN I DO THIS
ANOTHER TIME?

05:18.959 --> 05:20.417
ABSOLUTELY.

05:26.625 --> 05:29.041
YOU SLEPT HERE AGAIN
LAST NIGHT, DIDN'T YOU?

05:29.041 --> 05:29.917
DOESN'T THAT, LIKE,

05:29.917 --> 05:32.625
VIOLATE SOME
SORT OF HEALTH CODE?

05:32.625 --> 05:33.875
GOOD MORNING, AUDREY.

05:33.875 --> 05:35.583
I CAN ONLY ASSUME,
SINCE IT'S YOUR DAY OFF,

05:35.583 --> 05:37.917
THAT YOU CAME HERE
FOR A LITTLE BIT

05:37.917 --> 05:39.500
OF PLAYFUL BANTER
AND THE OPPORTUNITY

05:39.500 --> 05:40.208
TO CRITIQUE
MY PERSONAL HYGIENE.

05:40.208 --> 05:41.417
WHICH IS SWEET OF YOU,

05:41.417 --> 05:43.834
BUT YOU SHOULD
HAVE CALLED FIRST.

05:43.834 --> 05:44.959
CAN I HAVE
THAT OMELETTE?

05:44.959 --> 05:45.625
NO.

05:45.625 --> 05:47.583
WE HAD PLANS, YOU KNOW.

05:47.583 --> 05:48.583
YOU SAID YOU'D HELP ME.

05:48.583 --> 05:50.500
UH, RIGHT.
REFRESH MY MEMORY,

05:50.500 --> 05:52.166
THAT WAS THE BREAST
EXAM, RIGHT?

05:52.166 --> 05:53.458
NO. LEARNING MY LINES
FOR DAWSON'S MOVIE.

05:53.458 --> 05:56.166
WE TALKED ABOUT THIS
LAST NIGHT, REMEMBER?

05:56.166 --> 05:57.417
ONLY VAGUELY.

05:57.417 --> 05:59.333
AND TO TELL YOU THE
GOD'S HONEST, AUDREY,

05:59.333 --> 06:02.875
NOW IS REALLY NOT
THE BEST TIME FOR ME.

06:02.875 --> 06:03.959
Girl:
GOOD MORNING.

06:03.959 --> 06:06.708
WHAT'S
FOR BREAKFAST?

06:06.708 --> 06:09.041
AUDREY, I WOULD LIKE
TO INTRODUCE YOU

06:09.041 --> 06:10.917
TO MY GOOD FRIEND GINA.

06:10.917 --> 06:12.792
EXCUSE ME?

06:12.792 --> 06:13.792
WHAT?

06:13.792 --> 06:15.667
WHAT'S MY NAME?

06:15.667 --> 06:16.375
[COUGH]-INA.

06:16.375 --> 06:18.750
MY NAME IS RINA.

06:18.750 --> 06:20.875
R-I-N-A.

06:20.875 --> 06:22.083
WHICH IS WHAT
I SAID, RINA.

06:22.083 --> 06:24.542
DIDN'T I SAY "RINA", AUDREY?
YOU SAID "GINA."

06:26.125 --> 06:28.708
THANK YOU.

06:28.708 --> 06:31.083
OH, COME ON, SWEETHEART,
DON'T LEAVE ANGRY.

06:31.083 --> 06:32.667
OR AT LEAST
DON'T DRIVE ANGRY.

06:32.667 --> 06:33.500
HAVE A NICE LIFE,
STACEY!

06:36.875 --> 06:39.041
ON SECOND THOUGHT,

06:39.041 --> 06:40.834
THE OMELETTE'S YOURS.

06:45.208 --> 06:48.250
Polar Bear: JACK.

06:48.250 --> 06:48.500
MORNING.

06:51.083 --> 06:52.750
AHEM. HOW'S IT GOING, BRO?

06:52.750 --> 06:55.667
Polar Bear: WE'RE HEARING
THERE'S A KEGGER

06:55.667 --> 06:57.125
AT THE KAPPA MU PI  SORORITY.

06:57.125 --> 06:58.250
SO THOSE OF YOU INTERESTED

06:58.250 --> 06:59.500
IN GETTING SOME
NOOKY THIS EVENING,

06:59.500 --> 07:02.750
WE SHOULD MEET BACK HERE
AT, LET'S SAY... 11:00?

07:02.750 --> 07:03.959
BREAK.

07:11.917 --> 07:14.083
YOU OK?

07:14.083 --> 07:15.750
YEAH. I'M GOOD.

07:15.750 --> 07:16.750
THEY'RE TRYING
TO MAKE IT UP TO YOU.

07:16.750 --> 07:20.083
SMOOTH THINGS OVER.
I KNOW. I KNOW.

07:20.083 --> 07:21.291
YOU JUST GOTTA
LET 'EM BACK IN.

07:21.291 --> 07:22.458
SOUNDS GOOD IN THEORY,

07:22.458 --> 07:24.125
BUT IT'S HARD
TO FORGET THAT NIGHT.

07:24.125 --> 07:25.041
YOU GUYS
TOTALLY BAILED ON ME.

07:25.041 --> 07:26.291
YOU STEPPED
OVER THE LINE

07:26.291 --> 07:28.667
IN A BIG WAY THAT NIGHT, JACK.
I KNOW. I JUST...

07:28.667 --> 07:30.542
I FEEL LIKE THAT MOMENT
THAT I COULD HAVE

07:30.542 --> 07:33.917
GRACEFULLY APOLOGIZED
HAS KINDA PASSED ME BY.

07:33.917 --> 07:35.250
EVERY TIME
I'M AROUND THESE GUYS

07:35.250 --> 07:36.667
I FEEL LIKE AN IDIOT.

07:36.667 --> 07:38.458
WELL, STOP STRESSING.
YOU ARE  AN IDIOT.

07:38.458 --> 07:39.500
HMM?

07:39.500 --> 07:41.041
[LAUGHS]

07:42.667 --> 07:44.250
I KNOW YOU'RE A SNAKE
AND A CON ARTIST.

07:44.250 --> 07:45.458
I KNOW YOU'VE SLEPT YOUR WAY

07:45.458 --> 07:46.708
THROUGH THE
FEMALE STUDENT BODY

07:46.708 --> 07:48.000
AND ALMOST
HALF THE FACULTY.

07:48.000 --> 07:49.667
THE KIND OF BOY
WHO'LL BREAK YOUR HEART

07:49.667 --> 07:52.041
AND THEN START IN
ON YOUR SISTER.

07:52.041 --> 07:53.458
GOOD MORNING, SUNSHINE.

07:53.458 --> 07:55.792
IT'S OVERCAST
AND GREY.

07:55.792 --> 07:57.125
Jen: ♪ HMM HMM HMM ♪

07:57.125 --> 07:58.875
THERE, THAT'S THE SPIRIT.

07:58.875 --> 08:00.583
A WEEK AGO,
I SAW IT VERY CLEARLY.

08:00.583 --> 08:02.917
NOW I LOOK AT IT,
AND ALL I SEE

08:02.917 --> 08:05.834
ARE THESE HUGE,
NIGHTMARISH OBSTACLES.

08:05.834 --> 08:07.583
IT'S LIKE,
THE MOVIE'S DISAPPEARED,

08:07.583 --> 08:09.250
JUST GOTTEN LOST
SOMEWHERE ALONG THE WAY.
I DON'T KNOW.

08:09.250 --> 08:12.458
OR, MAYBE I HAVE.

08:12.458 --> 08:14.792
IT CAN'T BE THAT BAD,
CAN IT?

08:14.792 --> 08:16.959
[LAUGHS]
NOT THAT BAD?

08:16.959 --> 08:18.667
OK, THE ENDING DOESN'T WORK,

08:18.667 --> 08:20.500
BUT WE HAVE LESS
THAN 12 HOURS TO REWRITE IT

08:20.500 --> 08:23.208
BECAUSE THE LIGHTS
THEY WERE GONNA USE

08:23.208 --> 08:24.458
FOR THAT PARTICULAR SEQUENCE

08:24.458 --> 08:26.250
WE ONLY HAVE RENTED
UNTIL TOMORROW MORNING.

08:26.250 --> 08:27.458
[LAUGHS]

08:27.458 --> 08:28.750
BUT THE REAL PUNCH LINE IS,

08:28.750 --> 08:30.166
ALL OF THIS PALES
IN COMPARISON

08:30.166 --> 08:32.082
TO THE REAL PROBLEM.

08:32.082 --> 08:32.917
OK. WHAT'S
THE REAL PROBLEM?

08:32.917 --> 08:34.750
THE REAL PROBLEM
IS THAT OLIVER

08:34.750 --> 08:36.207
IS WITHOUT A DOUBT,

08:36.207 --> 08:40.041
THE MOST PATHETIC EXCUSE
FOR A THESPIAN THAT'S EVER BEEN.

08:40.041 --> 08:43.332
[SIGHS]

08:43.332 --> 08:46.417
OW!

08:46.417 --> 08:49.792
JACK AND GRAMS HAVE
MORE SEXUAL CHEMISTRY
THAN THESE TWO.

08:49.792 --> 08:51.792
HELLO, PEOPLE.

08:54.708 --> 08:56.708
WHAT? WHAT DID I MISS?

08:56.708 --> 08:58.458
HAVE A SEAT,
SKIPPER.

09:08.166 --> 09:09.959
IT'S TIME FOR US
TO THINK ABOUT

09:09.959 --> 09:10.625
WHAT'S BEST FOR THE MOVIE.

09:10.625 --> 09:12.375
I DON'T FOLLOW.

09:12.375 --> 09:13.458
HAVING WATCHED
SOME OF THE FOOTAGE,

09:13.458 --> 09:16.917
IT'S OCCURRED TO ME...

09:16.917 --> 09:18.417
IT'S POSSIBLE YOU'RE NOT
THE RIGHT ACTOR

09:18.417 --> 09:22.166
FOR THIS PARTICULAR ROLE.

09:22.166 --> 09:23.583
HMM.

09:24.708 --> 09:27.500
WELL, I'M THINKING
YOU'RE WRONG.

09:28.875 --> 09:30.667
BUT ON THE OTHER HAND,

09:30.667 --> 09:32.208
YOU ARE THE DIRECTOR,

09:32.208 --> 09:33.708
AND IF THIS BEHEMOTH

09:33.708 --> 09:35.291
HAS A PRAYER
OF GETTING DONE,

09:35.291 --> 09:37.333
IT'S GONNA BE BECAUSE
THE FINAL DECISION
ON EVERYTHING,

09:37.333 --> 09:40.542
INCLUDING THE CASTING,

09:40.542 --> 09:41.625
CAME FROM YOU.

09:41.625 --> 09:44.166
REALLY?
YOU'RE OK WITH THIS?

09:44.166 --> 09:45.166
ON THE FLIPSIDE,

09:45.166 --> 09:46.458
WE HAVE TO RECAST
THE PART TODAY

09:46.458 --> 09:48.583
IF WE'RE GONNA SHOOT
THE FINALE TONIGHT.

09:48.583 --> 09:50.583
WHERE ARE WE GONNA
FIND AN ACTOR WHO
FITS THE BILL, YOU KNOW?

09:50.583 --> 09:52.625
SOMEBODY'S WHO'S...

09:52.625 --> 09:57.250
SEXY, CHARISMATIC
AND ATTRACTIVE.

09:57.250 --> 09:58.542
AND NOT BURDENED
WITH A SOUL.

09:58.542 --> 09:59.917
EXACTLY.

09:59.917 --> 10:01.208
WHERE WE GONNA FIND
A GUY LIKE THAT
IN 6 HOURS?

10:01.208 --> 10:02.333
[LAUGHS]

10:02.333 --> 10:05.500
I USED TO DATE HIM.

10:08.458 --> 10:11.125
THAT'S NOT A BAD IDEA.

10:11.125 --> 10:12.333
OH, YES IT IS.

10:12.333 --> 10:15.291
IT'S A TERRIBLE IDEA.

10:16.583 --> 10:18.500
AND YOU WOULD NEVER
MAKE ME DO THAT,

10:18.500 --> 10:20.375
WOULD YOU, DAWSON?

10:21.917 --> 10:22.708
[GROAN]

10:25.583 --> 10:27.458
[LAUGHS]

10:27.458 --> 10:28.834
JEN LINDLEY.
HOW YA BEEN?

10:31.125 --> 10:32.917
BUSY.

10:32.917 --> 10:34.750
JUST TRYING
TO WRAP MY HEAD AROUND

10:34.750 --> 10:36.667
THIS WHOLE
"LEMON DIET COKE"
PHENOMENON.

10:36.667 --> 10:39.125
I KNEW IT. I KNEW YOU COULD
NEVER LIVE WITHOUT ME.

10:39.125 --> 10:40.625
HMM.

10:40.625 --> 10:42.208
OH, ON THE CONTRARY,

10:42.208 --> 10:44.000
I ACTUALLY PLAN TO SPEND
THE REST OF MY LIFE

10:44.000 --> 10:46.291
LIVING WITHOUT YOU,
CHARLIE, BUT...

10:46.291 --> 10:48.542
I NEED A FAVOR.

10:48.542 --> 10:50.625
A FAVOR?

10:50.625 --> 10:54.000
NOW WHY ON EARTH
WOULD I DO YOU A FAVOR?

10:54.000 --> 10:56.458
YOU GET TO MAKE OUT
WITH A REALLY HOT GIRL.

10:56.458 --> 10:57.750
OK. STEP INTO MY OFFICE

11:08.417 --> 11:10.583
THE GUY IS UNBELIEVABLE.

11:10.583 --> 11:13.250
I KNOW. HE COULDN'T EVEN
REMEMBER HER FIRST NAME.

11:13.250 --> 11:15.542
NOT HER LAST NAME-- HER LAST
NAME I MIGHT UNDERSTAND.

11:15.542 --> 11:17.000
I'VE SLEPT WITH GUYS
WHOSE LAST NAMES

11:17.000 --> 11:18.458
HAVE ESCAPED ME THE MORNING
AFTER, BUT HER FIRST NAME?

11:18.458 --> 11:21.834
WHO?
WHAT? WAIT...

11:21.834 --> 11:22.333
WHO ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

11:22.333 --> 11:23.500
WILDER.

11:23.500 --> 11:26.667
RIGHT. WILDER. UNBELIEVABLE.

11:26.667 --> 11:27.750
SO I'M STANDING THERE,

11:27.750 --> 11:29.708
READY TO SAY
EVERYTHING I NEVER SAID,

11:29.708 --> 11:30.834
AND THEN HE PULLS THIS

11:30.834 --> 11:32.375
JEDI-MIND-TRICK,
AND SUDDENLY,

11:32.375 --> 11:33.583
I CAN'T EVEN
REMEMBER WHO I AM.

11:33.583 --> 11:34.667
YOU'RE JOEY POTTER.

11:34.667 --> 11:36.959
I REFUSE TO BECOME
ANOTHER ONE OF HIS GROUPIES.

11:36.959 --> 11:39.417
COMPLETELY INFATUATED, REDUCED
TO A BABBLING IDIOT

11:39.417 --> 11:40.500
AT THE MENTION
OF HIS NAME.

11:40.500 --> 11:42.000
MAY I, UM...

11:42.000 --> 11:43.166
BE BRUTALLY HONEST?

11:43.166 --> 11:45.834
LIKE YOU'VE EVER BEEN
ANYTHING BUT?

11:45.834 --> 11:47.959
YOU ARE COMPLETELY
INFATUATED WITH HIM,

11:47.959 --> 11:50.250
AND YOU HAVE BEEN REDUCED
TO A BABBLING IDIOT

11:50.250 --> 11:51.667
AT THE MERE MENTION
OF HIS NAME.

11:51.667 --> 11:53.375
BUT I'M NOT SO SURE
THAT'S A BAD THING.

11:53.375 --> 11:55.875
HOW COULD IT NOT BE
A BAD THING, AUDREY?

11:55.875 --> 11:58.375
ONCE UPON A TIME,
I HAD THIS...

11:58.375 --> 12:00.792
AMAZING MENTOR.

12:00.792 --> 12:03.083
SOMEONE WHO BELIEVED
IN ME AND RESPECTED ME

12:03.083 --> 12:04.291
AND WE WERE FRIENDS.
GOOD FRIENDS.

12:04.291 --> 12:06.083
AND WHENEVER YOU WOULD ALLUDE
TO SOME AFFAIR

12:06.083 --> 12:09.250
BETWEEN TEACHER AND STUDENT,
I WOULD JUST DISMISS IT.

12:09.250 --> 12:11.041
WELL, THE LADY DOTH
PROTEST TOO MUCH.

12:11.041 --> 12:12.250
I HAVE
TO DROP HIS CLASS.

12:12.250 --> 12:14.208
I MEAN, SHOULD I DROP
HIS CLASS? I DON'T KNOW.

12:14.208 --> 12:15.542
ARE YOU ASKING
FOR MY ADVICE,

12:15.542 --> 12:16.667
OR ARE YOU
HAVING A SOLILOQUY?

12:16.667 --> 12:17.708
WHAT'S THE ALTERNATIVE?

12:17.708 --> 12:18.875
I SPEND
THE REST OF THE YEAR

12:18.875 --> 12:20.667
ANGSTING OVER SOME GUY
I CAN'T BE WITH?

12:20.667 --> 12:22.375
I'VE BEEN THERE.
IT'S EXCRUCIATING.

12:22.375 --> 12:25.458
BUNNY... BREATHE.

12:25.458 --> 12:26.583
ASK YOURSELF SOMETHING,

12:26.583 --> 12:27.750
WHEN WAS THE LAST TIME

12:27.750 --> 12:31.542
YOU FELT AS COMPLETELY
AND TOTALLY ALIVE

12:31.542 --> 12:33.417
AS YOU DO RIGHT NOW?

12:35.041 --> 12:37.250
[BOTH LAUGH]

12:38.166 --> 12:40.250
WHO WERE
YOU TALKING ABOUT?

12:40.250 --> 12:42.875
[GROANS]

12:46.333 --> 12:47.708
YO.

12:47.708 --> 12:48.750
HEY. THOUGHT YOU WERE GOING

12:48.750 --> 12:50.750
WITH THE OTHER GUYS
TO THE ATHLETIC CENTER?

12:50.750 --> 12:52.083
PICK UP ON
THE GYMNASTICS TEAM?

12:52.083 --> 12:54.417
YOU KNOW, TEENAGE GIRLS
SLAMMING THEIR PELVISES

12:54.417 --> 12:56.208
INTO THE UNEVEN BARS
AT 80-MILES-AN-HOUR.

12:56.208 --> 12:57.917
I THINK THAT'D BE
RIGHT UP YOUR ALLEY.

12:57.917 --> 12:59.417
NO, I HAD WORK TO DO,

12:59.417 --> 13:00.625
SO I FIGURED
I'D GET STARTED
WITH PUTTING IT OFF.

13:00.625 --> 13:02.875
[LAUGHS]
YEAH.

13:02.875 --> 13:04.500
PROCRASTINATION...

13:06.250 --> 13:08.875
IT'S THE ONLY SKILL
WE EVER LEARN IN COLLEGE.

13:08.875 --> 13:10.792
AIN'T IT A LITTLE EARLY
IN THE DAY TO START
KNOCKING 'EM BACK?

13:10.792 --> 13:13.291
ONLY IF YOU'RE
DOING IT ALONE.

13:13.291 --> 13:16.041
BESIDES, YOU AND I HAVE
SOME UNFINISHED BUSINESS.

13:16.041 --> 13:17.125
OH, DO WE?

13:17.125 --> 13:17.583
YES, WE DO.

13:17.583 --> 13:19.458
MADDEN 2002.

13:19.458 --> 13:20.875
OHHHH.

13:20.875 --> 13:22.542
YEAH, YOUR PATRIOTS
KICKED MY BEARS

13:22.542 --> 13:24.458
INTO A DIFFERENT TIME ZONE
LAST TIME THEY MET,

13:24.458 --> 13:26.208
AND I THINK WE'RE READY
FOR SOME REVENGE.

13:26.208 --> 13:27.750
GET SET
FOR SOME DISAPPOINTMENT,

13:27.750 --> 13:29.458
BECAUSE WE'RE GONNA
KICK YOUR ASS MORE.

13:29.458 --> 13:31.458
[LAUGHS]
NO, NO. I DON'T THINK SO,

13:33.083 --> 13:36.458
"YOU'RE FALLING
IN LOVE WITH ME."

13:36.458 --> 13:38.792
"I CAN'T SAY YOU'RE
LACKING FOR CONFIDENCE."

13:38.792 --> 13:40.583
"THAT'S NOT TRUE."

13:40.583 --> 13:42.417
BLAH, BLAH, BLAH.
BLAH, BLAH, BLAH.

13:42.417 --> 13:45.625
"DOESN'T CHANGE THE FACT
THAT YOU'RE FALLING
IN LOVE WITH ME."

13:45.625 --> 13:47.250
"NOW HOW CAN YOU BE SO SURE?

13:47.250 --> 13:48.625
"I MEAN, HOW DO YOU KNOW
I'M NOT GONNA JUST USE YOU UP

13:48.625 --> 13:51.166
"AND THROW YOU OUT.

13:51.166 --> 13:53.125
THAT'S WHAT
I'VE ALWAYS DONE."

13:53.125 --> 13:54.166
"YOU CAN SLEEP WITH..."

13:54.166 --> 13:56.583
BLAH, BLAH, BLAH.
BLAH, BLAH, BLAH--

13:56.583 --> 13:57.583
"NOT EVEN YOU."

13:57.583 --> 14:01.166
"I DIDN'T KNOW.

14:01.166 --> 14:04.500
I'VE NEVER WANTED ANYTHING
LIKE THIS BEFORE."

14:04.500 --> 14:05.625
UH...

14:05.625 --> 14:08.250
"NEITHER HAVE I."

14:08.250 --> 14:10.166
A WORLD OF PAIN.

14:10.166 --> 14:11.667
CHARLIE,
ONE STEP CLOSER,

14:11.667 --> 14:12.667
AND YOU'RE ENTERING
A WORLD OF PAIN.

14:12.667 --> 14:15.166
YOU KNOW, DAWSON, BUDDY,

14:15.166 --> 14:17.166
IT'S DIFFICULT TO REALLY
BECOME THE CHARACTER

14:17.166 --> 14:19.208
WHEN SHE IS NOT GIVING ME
ANYTHING TO WORK WITH.

14:19.208 --> 14:22.333
ACTING TIP: IT'S CALLED
USING YOUR IMAGINATION.

14:22.333 --> 14:24.333
OK. YOU KNOW,
I'VE SEEN ENOUGH.

14:24.333 --> 14:25.500
SO, AH, JEN...

14:25.500 --> 14:27.333
THANK YOU, SWEETHEART.

14:29.125 --> 14:31.834
UM, CHARLIE,
WOULD YOU MIND JUST...

14:31.834 --> 14:33.333
STEPPING IN THE OTHER
ROOM FOR A SECOND.

14:33.333 --> 14:35.792
YEAH.

14:37.166 --> 14:39.375
SO IS THIS GONNA BE
AWKWARD FOR YOU,

14:39.375 --> 14:41.208
YOUR GIRLFRIEND'S EX
STARRING IN OUR FLICK?

14:41.208 --> 14:43.750
I'M RUNNING OUT
OF OPTIONS HERE.

14:43.750 --> 14:44.792
I GOTTA SAY...

14:44.792 --> 14:47.041
HE'S PRETTY DECENT.

14:47.041 --> 14:48.667
I MEAN...

14:48.667 --> 14:50.542
IF YOU'RE GOING
FOR THE BRUTALLY HANDSOME,

14:50.542 --> 14:52.208
RIPPLING ABS,
TONY SCOTT-VERSION OF ME,

14:52.208 --> 14:53.875
HE'S AS GOOD
AS WE'RE GONNA GET, RIGHT?

14:53.875 --> 14:55.041
RIGHT.
YEAH.

14:55.041 --> 14:56.000
OK, SO WE USE HIM.

14:56.000 --> 14:57.333
YES.
PROBLEM SOLVED.

14:57.333 --> 14:59.166
NOW ALL I HAVE
TO DO IS OVERHAUL
THE ENDING

14:59.166 --> 15:00.500
AND WE MIGHT
GET THIS DONE.

15:00.500 --> 15:01.834
[LAUGHS]
HEAVENS TO BETSY.

15:01.834 --> 15:04.000
FIRST, YOU TAKE AWAY
MY STARRING ROLE,

15:04.000 --> 15:04.875
AND NOW YOU WANT
TO REWRITE MY ENDING?

15:04.875 --> 15:06.083
IT DOESN'T MAKE SENSE.

15:06.083 --> 15:08.583
ACTUALLY,
IT'S FRIGGIN' BRILLIANT.

15:08.583 --> 15:11.166
FIRST, SHE BREAKS UP WITH HIM,
BREAKS HIS HEART,

15:11.166 --> 15:13.291
THEN HE BLOW HER AWAY
WITH A .22.

15:13.291 --> 15:14.625
POETIC JUSTICE.

15:14.625 --> 15:16.834
I USED TO THINK IT WAS GREAT.
IT WAS PERFECT. BUT...

15:16.834 --> 15:20.125
HAVING SEEN THE FOOTAGE--
YADA, YADA, YADA.

15:20.125 --> 15:21.166
SO...

15:21.166 --> 15:23.083
DID I GET THE PART, OR WHAT?

15:23.083 --> 15:24.208
WELL, THAT DEPENDS.

15:24.208 --> 15:25.875
CAN YOU LEARN YOUR LINES
IN 3 HOURS?

15:25.875 --> 15:27.583
UH, BETTER MAKE THAT 2.

15:27.583 --> 15:29.208
HMM.

15:29.208 --> 15:31.583
ALL RIGHT.

15:31.583 --> 15:34.125
Eric: ALL MY DUDES,
THEY GO TO THESE PARTIES
EVERY NIGHT

15:34.125 --> 15:36.792
LOOKING FOR THEIR
NEXT GIRLFRIEND.
AND FOR WHAT?

15:36.792 --> 15:38.208
HUH? SO THEY
CAN HAVE SOME CHICK

15:38.208 --> 15:39.792
WHO'S GONNA BITCH AT 'EM
IN THE MORNING?

15:39.792 --> 15:41.750
MAKE THEM
WATCH NOTTING HILL
OVER AND OVER?

15:41.750 --> 15:42.583
NO. FORGET THAT.
THEY CAN KEEP THEIR KEG.

15:42.583 --> 15:44.875
[BOTH LAUGH]

15:44.875 --> 15:46.250
I LIKED NOTTING HILL.

15:46.250 --> 15:49.000
[BOTH LAUGH]

15:57.208 --> 16:00.041
DUDE.
YEAH?

16:02.291 --> 16:04.208
WHAT WAS IT LIKE
WHEN YOU REALIZED
YOU WERE GAY?

16:07.542 --> 16:09.125
WELL, IT WASN'T
LIKE THAT, YOU KNOW?

16:09.125 --> 16:12.375
IT WASN'T LIKE
I WOKE UP ONE MORNING

16:12.375 --> 16:14.125
FROM A ESPECIALLY NASTY DREAM
ABOUT ROBERT DOWNEY JR.

16:14.125 --> 16:17.750
AND I SAID TO MYSELF,
"HEY, I MUST BE GAY."

16:19.458 --> 16:21.166
WELL,
WHAT WAS IT LIKE?

16:21.166 --> 16:23.125
[SIGHS]

16:23.125 --> 16:23.750
WELL, YOU KNOW...

16:23.750 --> 16:26.500
SO MANY PEOPLE JUST...

16:26.500 --> 16:28.041
THEY SPEND SO MUCH
OF THEIR LIVES

16:28.041 --> 16:31.166
JUST LOCKED UP IN THIS CAGE
INSIDE THEMSELVES.

16:32.792 --> 16:33.625
AND THEY NEVER EVEN KNOW

16:33.625 --> 16:35.792
THAT THEY HAVE
THE KEY ALL ALONG.

16:37.875 --> 16:40.375
THAT'S HOW IT WAS FOR ME.

16:40.375 --> 16:42.708
I CAN'T TELL YOU WHEN
I FIRST REALIZED IT, YOU KNOW.

16:42.708 --> 16:44.417
I DON'T KNOW. AT SOME LEVEL,

16:44.417 --> 16:46.208
I THINK I'VE ALWAYS KNOWN IT.

16:46.208 --> 16:47.291
PROBABLY JUST LIKE

16:47.291 --> 16:49.291
YOU'VE ALWAYS KNOWN
YOU'RE STRAIGHT.

16:49.291 --> 16:52.291
IT WASN'T ABOUT
REALIZING THAT I WAS GAY,

16:52.291 --> 16:56.041
IT WAS ABOUT REALIZING
THAT IT WAS ALL RIGHT.

16:58.166 --> 17:00.500
YOU'RE AN
AMAZING GUY, JACK.

17:00.500 --> 17:02.667
YOU KNOW THAT?
YOU REALLY ARE.

17:11.625 --> 17:13.583
[SIGHS]

17:17.333 --> 17:21.834
YOU'RE THE KIND OF GUY
THAT I WANNA BE.

17:32.291 --> 17:34.542
UM...

17:34.542 --> 17:36.291
DO YOU, UH...

17:36.291 --> 17:36.875
DO YOU WANNA
WATCH SOME MORE TV?

17:36.875 --> 17:38.542
I, UH...I-I-I THINK

17:38.542 --> 17:41.542
THE WORLD'S MOST HORRIFYING
BUNGEE-ACCIDENTS  IS ON.

17:41.542 --> 17:44.250
UM...

17:44.250 --> 17:46.834
NO, I HAVE WORK TO DO.

17:46.834 --> 17:48.083
COME ON, MAN.
YOU'RE NOT GONNA--

17:48.083 --> 17:49.375
YOU'RE NOT GONNA
DO IT NOW.

17:49.375 --> 17:50.834
YEAH. I HAVE TO. OK?

17:50.834 --> 17:51.542
I'M--I'M--I'M GONNA GO.

17:51.542 --> 17:55.250
OK?

17:55.250 --> 17:57.708
YEAH, I'LL SEE YA.

18:18.000 --> 18:19.000
HEY.

18:19.000 --> 18:20.834
YOU SELLING
GIRL SCOUT COOKIES?

18:20.834 --> 18:22.333
DO YOU HAVE ANY
OF THE COCONUT ONES

18:22.333 --> 18:25.417
WITH THE CHOCOLATE
AND THE CARAMEL?
I LOVE THOSE.

18:25.417 --> 18:27.250
ACTUALLY, I FIGURED OUT
WHAT I WANT TO SAY.

18:27.250 --> 18:29.333
EXCELLENT.
I'LL ALERT THE MEDIA.

18:32.417 --> 18:34.083
DO YOU THINK
IT'D BE POSSIBLE

18:34.083 --> 18:36.000
TO LOSE THE OBNOXIOUS GLIB
FOR 5 SECONDS?

18:36.000 --> 18:39.959
YES. YES, OF COURSE.
IT IS POSSIBLE. SURE.

18:39.959 --> 18:41.166
I'M SORRY. GO AHEAD.

18:41.166 --> 18:42.125
UH...

18:42.125 --> 18:43.959
I WANT TO SAY...

18:45.250 --> 18:46.750
I'M SORRY YOU KISSED ME.

18:46.750 --> 18:49.583
OH, MY GOD, JOEY,

18:49.583 --> 18:51.041
I CAN'T EVEN BEGIN
TO APOLOGIZE ABOUT THAT.

18:51.041 --> 18:54.000
I'M NOT HERE
FOR AN APOLOGY.

18:54.000 --> 18:55.208
I DIDN'T WANT ONE
THAT NIGHT,

18:55.208 --> 18:56.583
I DON'T WANT ONE NOW.

18:58.792 --> 19:03.000
WELL...IN A MINUTE,
I'M GOING TO WALK OVER THERE

19:03.000 --> 19:05.875
TO WHERE YOU ARE AND, UM,

19:05.875 --> 19:07.417
I'M GONNA SHAKE YOUR HAND
IN A VERY MASCULINE WAY.

19:07.417 --> 19:11.625
WE'RE GONNA HAVE THIS
LITTLE SILENT UNDERSTANDING

19:11.625 --> 19:16.208
AND THEN I'M JUST GONNA
TURN AROUND AND WALK AWAY.

19:17.500 --> 19:18.583
WHAT ABOUT MY CLASS?

19:18.583 --> 19:21.792
UH, I DON'T THINK
I CAN BE A PART OF IT,

19:21.792 --> 19:24.125
NOT NOW.

19:24.125 --> 19:26.625
WELL,
NO GREAT LOSS THERE.

19:26.625 --> 19:28.959
YOU KNOW WHAT?

19:28.959 --> 19:31.000
SCREW YOU.

19:31.000 --> 19:32.542
CLEVER, JOEY.

19:32.542 --> 19:36.458
NO. WHAT I MEANT
WAS YOU'RE GONNA
DO GREAT...

19:36.458 --> 19:40.083
WITH OR WITHOUT
MY WORKSHOP.

19:41.583 --> 19:42.583
OH.

19:45.041 --> 19:46.917
THAT'S WHAT YOU MEANT.

19:46.917 --> 19:49.208
JOEY, YOU'VE GOT IT.

19:49.208 --> 19:50.834
THE GIFT. THE TOUCH.

19:50.834 --> 19:52.000
WHATEVER YOU WANT
TO CALL IT.

19:52.000 --> 19:53.000
I DON'T. YOU DO.

19:53.000 --> 19:54.583
IT'S A BINARY
DISTINCTION.

19:54.583 --> 19:57.333
SO ALL
THE WASHED UP HACKS

19:57.333 --> 19:58.959
TURNED
ENGLISH PROFESSORS

19:58.959 --> 20:01.083
CAN WAX POETIC UNTIL
THE COWS COME HOME.

20:01.083 --> 20:03.875
IN THE END...

20:03.875 --> 20:06.375
YOUR TALENTS
AND YOUR INSTINCTS

20:06.375 --> 20:08.417
ARE THE ONLY THINGS
THAT REALLY MATTER.

20:13.041 --> 20:15.375
YOU KNOW,
YOU'RE REALLY ANNOYING.

20:15.375 --> 20:16.458
'CAUSE EVERY TIME

20:16.458 --> 20:19.959
I'M READY TO DO
THE SMART, SENSIBLE THING,

20:19.959 --> 20:25.208
YOU GO AND YOU
SAY SOMETHING THAT MAKES ME...

20:25.208 --> 20:27.000
MAKES YOU WHAT?

20:27.000 --> 20:30.667
NOT WANT TO GO AWAY.

20:38.458 --> 20:40.667
Audrey: OK. SO,
LET'S DO IT ONE
MORE TIME,

20:40.667 --> 20:43.041
BUT THIS TIME, I'M NOT
JUST GONNA SAY THE LINES,

20:43.041 --> 20:44.166
I'M REALLY
GONNA ACT THEM.

20:44.166 --> 20:44.834
YOU WARNING ME?

20:44.834 --> 20:46.708
NO.

20:46.708 --> 20:48.333
I JUST WANT YOU
TO PAY ATTENTION

20:48.333 --> 20:49.083
SO YOU CAN GIVE ME
SOME NOTES.

20:49.083 --> 20:51.542
OK. WELL, I'M READY.

20:51.542 --> 20:54.792
JUST GIVE ME
A MINUTE, OK,
WILL YA?

20:54.792 --> 20:56.750
BRING IT! BRING IT!
BRING IT ON!

20:56.750 --> 20:57.208
BRING IT!

20:57.208 --> 20:58.458
WHEW.

21:08.333 --> 21:11.333
YOU'RE NOT SO TOUGH,
YOU KNOW.

21:13.041 --> 21:14.083
UH, "WELL, I PICKED
THE LOCK TO GET IN HERE.

21:14.083 --> 21:16.500
THAT'S PRETTY TOUGH."

21:18.875 --> 21:21.083
YOU'RE FALLING IN LOVE
WITH ME.

21:21.083 --> 21:23.417
"I CAN'T SAY YOU'RE
LACKING FOR CONFIDENCE."

21:23.417 --> 21:27.834
NO. THAT'S NOT TRUE.

21:27.834 --> 21:29.000
I AM LACKING.

21:29.000 --> 21:32.875
I'M VERY INSECURE...

21:32.875 --> 21:35.291
BUT THAT DOESN'T
CHANGE THE FACT

21:35.291 --> 21:36.542
THAT YOU'RE
FALLING IN LOVE WITH ME.

21:39.250 --> 21:41.375
UH...

21:41.375 --> 21:42.708
"HOW CAN YOU BE SO SURE?

21:42.708 --> 21:44.625
"HOW DO YOU KNOW I'M NOT
JUST GONNA USE YOU UP

21:44.625 --> 21:45.708
"AND THROW YOU AWAY?

21:45.708 --> 21:47.166
IT'S WHAT
I'VE ALWAYS DONE."

21:47.166 --> 21:51.250
YOU CAN SLEEP
WITH ALL THE RIGHT GIRLS

21:51.250 --> 21:54.500
AND TAKE
ALL THE RIGHT DRUGS,

21:54.500 --> 21:57.083
BUT IN THE END...

21:57.083 --> 21:57.583
YOU'LL STILL BE ALONE.

22:01.000 --> 22:02.458
IT DOESN'T MATTER
WHAT ANYBODY SAYS, GAGE.

22:02.458 --> 22:06.500
NOBODY WANTS TO BE ALONE.
NOT EVEN YOU.

22:11.458 --> 22:13.959
WAIT! WAIT!

22:13.959 --> 22:16.083
I'M NOT GONNA DO THIS!

22:16.083 --> 22:17.583
UH, WELL, NO,
OF COURSE NOT.

22:17.583 --> 22:19.166
ME, NEITHER.

22:19.166 --> 22:21.667
BECAUSE...

22:21.667 --> 22:22.667
BECAUSE IT WOULD BE WRONG.

22:22.667 --> 22:24.834
WELL,
IT'S OBVIOUSLY WRONG.

22:24.834 --> 22:26.000
THAT'S WHY WE STOPPED.

22:26.000 --> 22:26.834
SO...

22:26.834 --> 22:30.834
SO...

22:30.834 --> 22:32.083
[SIGHS]

22:32.083 --> 22:34.792
DO YOU HAVE
ANY NOTES?

22:47.750 --> 22:48.959
CUT. CUT.
Dawson: CUT.

22:48.959 --> 22:50.375
I'M SORRY, OK?

22:50.375 --> 22:52.333
IT'S JUST
THAT MY CO-STAR

22:52.333 --> 22:53.375
CHARLIE SHEEN
OVER HERE,

22:53.375 --> 22:55.208
IS RAMMING
HIS TONGUE
DOWN MY THROAT.

22:55.208 --> 22:57.041
I FEEL LIKE
HE'S LOOKING FOR
MY DIAPHRAGM.

22:57.041 --> 22:58.375
FOILED AGAIN.

22:58.375 --> 23:00.875
Dawson:
OK, WE'RE GONNA
TAKE IT FROM, UH,

23:00.875 --> 23:02.708
JUST BEFORE
THE KISS. ALL RIGHT?

23:02.708 --> 23:05.583
AND, UH, PACE? I SEE THE BOOM
DIP IN AND OUT OF MY FRAME,

23:05.583 --> 23:06.500
I BEGIN TO FORGET
OUR FRIENDSHIP.

23:06.500 --> 23:09.875
OK.
ALL RIGHT. PICTURE'S UP.

23:09.875 --> 23:11.333
AND MARKER.

23:11.333 --> 23:14.375
14 BAKER, TAKE 12.

23:14.375 --> 23:16.667
AND...ACTION.

23:32.542 --> 23:34.208
I DIDN'T...

23:34.208 --> 23:37.291
I NEVER WANTED ANY...

23:37.291 --> 23:39.458
I'M SORRY.
CAN WE DO THAT DIFFERENT?

23:39.458 --> 23:40.625
IT KIND OF GOT AWAY
FROM ME.

23:40.625 --> 23:42.750
STILL ROLLING.
WHENEVER YOU'RE READY.

23:56.083 --> 23:58.917
I DIDN'T KNOW.

23:58.917 --> 24:01.834
I NEVER WANTED ANYTHING
LIKE THIS BEFORE.

24:01.834 --> 24:03.458
NEITHER HAVE I.

24:06.500 --> 24:08.417
LINE.

24:08.417 --> 24:10.875
"I'M AFRAID
OF FALLING."

24:13.375 --> 24:14.583
I'M AFRAID OF--

24:14.583 --> 24:16.458
WOULD GAGE REALLY SAY--

24:16.458 --> 24:18.125
FOR THE LOVE OF GOD,
JUST SAY IT.

24:22.000 --> 24:24.125
I'M AFRAID OF FALLING.

24:24.125 --> 24:26.542
DON'T WORRY.
I'LL CATCH YOU.

24:31.291 --> 24:32.667
AND CUT.

24:32.667 --> 24:33.959
OW. OW! SHE HIT ME
ON THE EAR.

24:33.959 --> 24:36.542
I'M SORRY. I CAN'T
WORK LIKE THIS, OK?

24:36.542 --> 24:38.333
IT'S COMPLETELY
UNPROFESSIONAL.

24:38.333 --> 24:40.125
AND IT'S JUST--
IT'S TOO INTENSE

24:40.125 --> 24:42.834
WITH YOU STANDING
RIGHT THERE NEXT
TO ME.

24:43.917 --> 24:46.917
YOU'RE A TERRIBLE
BOOM OPERATOR.

25:00.291 --> 25:01.834
REMEMBER
THAT UNCOMFORTABLE VIBE

25:01.834 --> 25:03.000
YOU WERE SENSING
IN CLASS?

25:03.000 --> 25:04.166
YES.

25:04.166 --> 25:05.000
GOOD THING
WE DEALT WITH IT.

25:05.000 --> 25:06.500
YEAH.
IT'S A GOOD THING,

25:06.500 --> 25:08.875
BECAUSE NOW THE 2 OF US
ALONE IN YOUR HOUSE--

25:08.875 --> 25:11.417
I'M SO RELIEVED
THAT THERE'S
NO AWKWARD TENSION.

25:11.417 --> 25:13.750
WE CAN JUST RELAX.

25:13.750 --> 25:15.500
YEAH, YEAH.
I'VE NEVER BEEN
THIS RELAXED.

25:15.500 --> 25:17.542
I--I MIGHT
FALL ASLEEP.

25:17.542 --> 25:20.667
WE'RE BEING SARCASTIC.

25:20.667 --> 25:22.792
LOOK, JOEY,
THE THING IS--

25:22.792 --> 25:25.375
THE THING I WANTED
TO SAY TO YOU IS I--

25:25.375 --> 25:26.667
I CAN'T AFFORD
TO LOSE MY JOB.

25:26.667 --> 25:29.667
THAT'S THE LAST THING
THAT I WANT.

25:29.667 --> 25:30.667
BUT IT'S IMPORTANT
TO ME THAT YOU KNOW

25:30.667 --> 25:32.959
THAT WHAT HAPPENED
BETWEEN US--

25:32.959 --> 25:36.417
I'VE NEVER DONE
ANYTHING LIKE THAT
BEFORE.

25:36.417 --> 25:38.834
I KNOW.

25:42.375 --> 25:44.250
YOU KNOW,
JOEY POTTER, I--

25:44.250 --> 25:46.959
I DON'T THINK
I'VE EVER MET ANYONE
LIKE YOU.

25:46.959 --> 25:49.250
THAT'S WHAT ALL BOYS SAY.

25:49.250 --> 25:50.708
YEAH? WELL,
THEY'RE RIGHT.

25:50.708 --> 25:53.458
I WAS BEING
SARCASTIC AGAIN.

25:54.875 --> 25:57.125
WANNA HEAR MY EXAMPLE?

25:57.125 --> 25:59.083
HMM?

25:59.083 --> 26:02.542
MY EXAMPLE
OF AN INTERNAL CONFLICT

26:02.542 --> 26:06.917
BETWEEN MY IDEALS
AND DESIRES.

26:06.917 --> 26:08.834
ARE YOU SURE YOU DON'T
WANNA SAVE IT FOR CLASS?

26:11.500 --> 26:14.959
I THINK I WANNA
RUN IT BY YOU FIRST.

26:14.959 --> 26:18.083
FAIR ENOUGH.

26:19.333 --> 26:20.291
[CELL PHONE VIBRATING]

26:20.291 --> 26:22.834
YOU'RE VIBRATING.

26:27.583 --> 26:29.708
EXCUSE ME.

26:33.875 --> 26:37.875
HELLO? HI.

26:37.875 --> 26:40.667
WHAT'S GOING ON?

26:40.667 --> 26:43.250
RIGHT NOW?

26:43.250 --> 26:45.125
YEAH. I'LL BE RIGHT THERE.

26:48.667 --> 26:49.250
I HAVE TO GO.

26:49.250 --> 26:52.708
OK.

26:52.708 --> 26:54.667
SORRY.

26:54.667 --> 26:57.625
DON'T BE.

27:32.000 --> 27:33.333
BYE.

27:40.625 --> 27:40.959
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

27:46.208 --> 27:48.041
ERIC TOLD US
WHAT HAPPENED.

27:48.041 --> 27:50.375
WHAT ARE YOU GUYS
TALKING ABOUT?

27:50.375 --> 27:52.667
ERIC TOLD US
YOU TRIED TO KISS HIM.

27:52.667 --> 27:54.000
YOU CAN'T BE SERIOUS.

27:56.834 --> 27:58.875
OH, MY GOD, YOU ARE.

27:58.875 --> 28:00.834
Blossom:
PLEASE DON'T WASTE
EVERYONE'S TIME

28:00.834 --> 28:02.166
SCRAMBLING
TO DENY IT.

28:02.166 --> 28:04.250
IT'S BETTER
IF YOU JUST ADMIT
THE TRUTH.

28:04.250 --> 28:05.500
YOU'RE RIGHT.

28:05.500 --> 28:07.166
THANK YOU.

28:07.166 --> 28:10.375
'CAUSE, YOU KNOW,
I WAS JUST NANCYING
AROUND MY ROOM

28:10.375 --> 28:11.917
IN MY THIGH-HIGHS,
AND I THOUGHT TO MYSELF,

28:11.917 --> 28:14.125
"I'M GONNA LAY A WET ONE
ON AN UNSUSPECTING
FRATERNITY BROTHER,

28:14.125 --> 28:17.208
"BECAUSE THAT'S
A GREAT WAY
TO SMOOTH THINGS OVER

28:17.208 --> 28:18.166
WITH THE HOUSE."
JACK...

28:18.166 --> 28:20.417
IF YOU GUYS IMAGINE
JUST FOR A SECOND

28:20.417 --> 28:22.500
THAT I WOULD--COULD EVER
IN A MILLION YEARS

28:22.500 --> 28:24.333
DO ANYTHING LIKE THAT
TO ANY ONE OF YOU GUYS,

28:24.333 --> 28:26.000
THEN I GUESS YOU GUYS
NEVER KNEW ME AT ALL.

28:26.000 --> 28:28.041
WAIT A MINUTE. YOU WANT US
TO BELIEVE THAT ERIC,

28:28.041 --> 28:29.959
LIKE, FABRICATED
THIS WHOLE THING?

28:29.959 --> 28:32.667
[SCOFFS]
NO. WHAT I'M SAYING
IS THAT I DON'T CARE,

28:32.667 --> 28:34.125
BECAUSE IT WOULDN'T MATTER
IF I DID.

28:34.125 --> 28:34.875
YOU GUYS HAVE
MADE UP YOUR MINDS.

28:34.875 --> 28:35.708
YOU KNOW WHAT?
SO HAVE I.

28:35.708 --> 28:38.166
I'M MOVING OUT
OF THE HOUSE

28:38.166 --> 28:39.875
AND I'M NOT COMING BACK.
THAT'S NOT WHAT WE WANT, JACK.

28:39.875 --> 28:44.041
WELL, WITH ALL DUE RESPECT,
MY BROTHERS,

28:44.041 --> 28:45.750
GET OUT.

28:55.875 --> 28:57.667
SO, DAWSON,
LET'S SAY THAT--

28:57.667 --> 28:59.375
HYPOTHETICALLY
SPEAKING--

28:59.375 --> 29:00.875
I MIGHT HAVE
SOME INSIGHT

29:00.875 --> 29:03.333
INTO WHY YOUR INGÉNUE
IS SO EXASPERATED TODAY.

29:03.333 --> 29:06.583
AND LET'S ALSO SAY
THAT--HYPOTHETICALLY
SPEAKING--

29:06.583 --> 29:11.625
I MIGHT BE
MILDLY CULPABLE
FOR HER EXASPERATION.

29:12.792 --> 29:14.458
WHICH REALLY ISN'T
THAT IMPORTANT,

29:14.458 --> 29:16.375
I'M SURE IT'S NOTHING,
FORGET I MENTIONED IT.

29:16.375 --> 29:18.875
PACEY, MY PATIENCE
IS WEARING JUST
A LITTLE BIT THIN.

29:18.875 --> 29:22.291
OK, WELL, UH,
HERE'S THE THING.

29:22.291 --> 29:23.750
I KISSED HER.

29:23.750 --> 29:24.875
YOU IDIOT.
DIDN'T ANYBODY
EVER TELL YOU

29:24.875 --> 29:27.125
THE FIRST RULE
OF THE UNIVERSE?

29:27.125 --> 29:30.000
UH, YEAH.
THAT ENERGY IS CONSERVED.

29:30.000 --> 29:31.208
FIRST RULE
OF THE UNIVERSE,

29:31.208 --> 29:32.750
NEVER GET INVOLVED
WITH AN ACTRESS.

29:32.750 --> 29:35.583
HELP. IT'S TRYING TO THINK.

29:37.166 --> 29:39.625
LOOK, I JUST WANTED
TO OFFER A FEW IDEAS...

29:40.750 --> 29:43.750
PARTICULARLY IN THE WAY
OF MY CHARACTER.

29:43.750 --> 29:45.417
ARE YOU SERIOUSLY
GONNA GIVE ME A REASON

29:45.417 --> 29:46.917
TO SLAP THE SILLY OUT OF YOU?!
HEY.

29:46.917 --> 29:49.375
COME ON, SLIM. COME ON! 'CAUSE
I'M FEELIN' A LITTLE CRAZY!

29:49.375 --> 29:50.917
A LITTLE DEEP BREATH.

29:50.917 --> 29:52.583
SHE'S GOT MOXIE, THAT ONE.
THAT IS NOT--

29:52.583 --> 29:54.917
WHO'S THIS MOXIE?

29:54.917 --> 29:56.041
[SOFTLY]
I'M SORRY.

29:56.041 --> 29:57.417
QUIET THOUGHTS.
GOOD THOUGHTS.

29:57.417 --> 29:58.583
I'M OK.

29:58.583 --> 30:00.458
HEY, GUYS.

30:00.458 --> 30:01.542
JOEY.

30:01.542 --> 30:02.792
NOT A MOMENT
TOO SOON.

30:02.792 --> 30:04.417
UH, TAKE PACEY
BY FORCE, IF NECESSARY,

30:04.417 --> 30:06.250
AND EXTRACT AUDREY
FROM THE BATHROOM.

30:06.250 --> 30:07.750
ALL RIGHT. OLIVER...

30:07.750 --> 30:09.166
TAKE CHARLIE,
FIND A LITTLE CORNER,

30:09.166 --> 30:11.417
AND NOD VAGUELY
WHILE HE GIVES YOU HIS NOTES.

30:11.417 --> 30:13.125
UH, JEN.

30:13.125 --> 30:16.333
SWEETHEART,
I DON'T WANT YOU
TO HAVE AN EMBOLISM.

30:16.333 --> 30:17.625
DAWSON, HE'S EVIL.

30:17.625 --> 30:18.959
ISN'T IT
ENTIRELY POSSIBLE

30:18.959 --> 30:20.125
THAT HE IS
THE ANTICHRIST,

30:20.125 --> 30:22.083
PACKED INTO THE BODY
OF A HANDSOME MUSICIAN?

30:22.083 --> 30:22.792
I NEED YOU TO DO ME
A BIG FAVOR.

30:22.792 --> 30:24.458
YOU WANT ME TO KILL HIM.

30:24.458 --> 30:25.708
I NEED YOU TO GO HOME.

30:25.708 --> 30:28.041
RIGHT NOW. JUST--
JUST GATHER YOUR STUFF
AND LEAVE.

30:28.041 --> 30:30.875
IT'S THE ONLY WAY
I'M GONNA GET THIS DONE.

30:30.875 --> 30:33.000
BUT WHO WOULD DO
THE CLAPPY THING?

30:33.000 --> 30:34.917
WE'LL MANAGE.

30:41.291 --> 30:44.875
PACE, WHY DID DAWSON
INSIST YOU COME ALONG
ON THIS MISSION?

30:44.875 --> 30:46.708
DID SOMETHING HAPPEN
BETWEEN YOU AND AUDREY?

30:46.708 --> 30:48.834
NO. NO.
OF COURSE NOT.

30:48.834 --> 30:50.542
BECAUSE IF SOMETHING
HAPPENED BETWEEN US

30:50.542 --> 30:51.750
IT WOULD BE
A HORRIBLE, TERRIBLE
THING, RIGHT?

30:51.750 --> 30:55.208
PACEY,
YOU'RE AN IDIOT.

30:55.208 --> 30:57.166
OK. IF ONE MORE PERSON
CALLS ME AN IDIOT,

30:57.166 --> 30:59.291
I'M REALLY GONNA START
FEELING BAD ABOUT MYSELF.

30:59.291 --> 31:01.166
DON'T YOU THINK I'D
PREFER YOU HOOKING UP

31:01.166 --> 31:02.917
WITH SOMEONE AMAZING
LIKE AUDREY

31:02.917 --> 31:04.500
RATHER THAN
SOME RANDOM DITZ

31:04.500 --> 31:06.708
WHO'S NAME YOU
CAN'T EVEN REMEMBER
IN THE MORNING?

31:06.708 --> 31:08.667
I CAN REMEMBER HER NAME.

31:10.417 --> 31:13.708
Audrey: GO AWAY.
SEVERE FLOODING.
OUT OF ORDER.

31:13.708 --> 31:15.041
AUDREY, IT'S ME.

31:15.041 --> 31:16.750
I'M WITH PACEY.
WE'RE COMING IN.

31:16.750 --> 31:18.333
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?
I CAN'T GO IN THERE.

31:18.333 --> 31:20.417
THAT'S
THE LADIES ROOM.

31:20.417 --> 31:23.291
JOE--OW, OW, OW.

31:23.291 --> 31:26.166
[SNIFFLING]

31:26.166 --> 31:27.834
AUDREY, YOU LOOK GREAT
IN THAT DRESS.

31:27.834 --> 31:28.959
REALLY?

31:28.959 --> 31:31.291
NO. FORGET IT.

31:31.291 --> 31:32.750
I DON'T DESERVE
TO TALK TO YOU.

31:32.750 --> 31:34.041
I DON'T EVEN
DESERVE TO BE

31:34.041 --> 31:35.750
IN THE SAME
LAVATORY AS YOU.

31:35.750 --> 31:37.041
WHY, BECAUSE
YOU KISSED PACEY?

31:37.041 --> 31:40.708
WHAT? YOU TOLD HER?
HOW COULD YOU?

31:40.708 --> 31:42.000
AMATEUR.

31:42.000 --> 31:43.542
AUDREY,
PACEY DIDN'T TELL ME.

31:43.542 --> 31:45.625
I INTUITED.

31:45.625 --> 31:48.917
THAT'S AMAZING, JOEY.
YOU'RE VERY INTELLIGENT.

31:48.917 --> 31:50.542
NEXT STOP, ROCKET SCIENCE.
I'M NOT UPSET.

31:50.542 --> 31:53.041
WELL, YOU SHOULD BE.

31:53.041 --> 31:56.500
OUR FRIENDSHIP IS LIKE
THE SPECIAL-EST THING

31:56.500 --> 31:57.875
THAT I'VE FOUND SINCE
I CAME HERE.

31:57.875 --> 31:59.792
AND WHAT DO I DO?
I STEP ON IT.

31:59.792 --> 32:01.875
I BETRAY YOU. WHY?
BECAUSE I AM WEAK
WHEN IT COMES TO MEN.

32:01.875 --> 32:03.625
Joey: YOU'RE NOT.

32:03.625 --> 32:04.750
OK...

32:04.750 --> 32:06.875
MAYBE YOU ARE WEAK.

32:06.875 --> 32:08.458
BUT KISSING PACEY
IS NOT WEAK.

32:08.458 --> 32:10.250
IN FACT, IT COULD BE
THE SMARTEST THING

32:10.250 --> 32:12.166
EITHER ONE OF YOU HAS
DONE FOR A LONG TIME.

32:12.166 --> 32:13.166
REALLY?

32:13.166 --> 32:14.375
YOU THINK?

32:14.375 --> 32:16.417
I LOVE YOU.

32:16.417 --> 32:18.000
I LOVE YOU.

32:18.000 --> 32:19.375
I LOVE YOU BOTH
IN THE BEST, SIMPLEST WAY,

32:19.375 --> 32:23.291
AND ALL I CARE ABOUT IS
THAT YOU GUYS ARE HAPPY.

32:23.291 --> 32:25.542
YOU'RE LIKE...

32:25.542 --> 32:26.542
GIVING US PERMISSION?

32:26.542 --> 32:28.083
YOU DON'T NEED
MY PERMISSION.

32:28.083 --> 32:31.708
I'M GIVING YOU
MY BLESSING...

32:31.708 --> 32:34.375
FOR WHAT IT'S WORTH.

32:51.125 --> 32:52.875
I WANT YOU TO LISTEN
TO ME CLOSELY,

32:52.875 --> 32:55.625
BECAUSE YOU'RE NEVER
GONNA GET ANYTHING
LIKE THIS AGAIN.

32:55.625 --> 32:57.959
YOU KNOW THE TRUTH.

32:57.959 --> 33:00.500
YOU KNOW WHAT REALLY
HAPPENED IN THAT ROOM
AND WHAT DIDN'T,

33:00.500 --> 33:02.125
AND YOU'RE GONNA HAVE
TO LIVE WITH THAT.

33:04.542 --> 33:08.291
AND BELIEVE ME WHEN
I TELL YOU, ERIC...

33:08.291 --> 33:10.291
YOU'VE GOT SOME SERIOUS
ISSUES TO DEAL WITH,

33:10.291 --> 33:12.083
AND YOU NEED
SOME SERIOUS HELP.

33:16.959 --> 33:19.708
I REALLY HOPE YOU FIND IT.

33:56.125 --> 33:57.834
THIS IS KIND
OF BEAUTIFUL.

33:57.834 --> 34:00.917
SHE SAYS,
AS SHE EXITS
CAMERA RIGHT.

34:02.959 --> 34:06.041
SO IF THERE ARE
NO FURTHER CRISES

34:06.041 --> 34:07.542
YOU NEED ME
TO BAIL YOU OUT OF--

34:07.542 --> 34:09.333
NOT UNLESS YOU CAN
FIX THE ENDING.

34:09.333 --> 34:10.708
WHAT'S WRONG
WITH THE ENDING?

34:10.708 --> 34:12.542
I'M NOT EVEN REALLY
SURE THAT IT'S WRONG.

34:12.542 --> 34:15.375
I'M JUST...

34:15.375 --> 34:15.750
UNSURE?

34:15.750 --> 34:17.041
YEAH.

34:17.041 --> 34:19.542
WELL, IT'S
A LOVE STORY, RIGHT?

34:19.542 --> 34:20.958
UH-HUH.

34:20.958 --> 34:23.041
SO DO THEY END UP
HAPPILY EVER AFTER
OR NOT SO MUCH?

34:23.041 --> 34:26.417
NOT SO MUCH.
HE KILLS HER.

34:26.417 --> 34:29.083
OH. A LITTLE DEPRESSING.

34:29.083 --> 34:31.333
A LITTLE CYNICAL
FOR THE DAWSON I KNOW.

34:31.333 --> 34:33.291
APPARENTLY,
I'M IN MY DARK PERIOD.

34:33.291 --> 34:35.917
IF THAT'S
REALLY TRUE, WHY ARE YOU
SO RELUCTANT TO FILM IT?

34:35.917 --> 34:37.708
'CAUSE PART OF ME WISHES
I COULD STILL BE

34:37.708 --> 34:40.667
THAT EMBARRASSING,
ROMANTIC KID.

34:40.667 --> 34:43.083
YOU KNOW,
THE ONE WHO BELIEVED
WITH SUCH CONVICTION

34:43.083 --> 34:44.625
IN THE GOSPEL
ACCORDING TO SPIELBERG.

34:44.625 --> 34:46.083
YOU KNOW, I'M HAVING
TROUBLE MUSTERING

34:46.083 --> 34:49.917
ANYTHING RESEMBLING
SENTIMENTALITY
OR CORN OR...

34:49.917 --> 34:52.625
FOR LACK OF
A BETTER WORD, HOPE.

34:52.625 --> 34:53.750
I WAS AT
THE BUS STATION ONE TIME

34:53.750 --> 34:57.750
AND SOMEONE HAD WRITTEN
THESE WORDS ON A BENCH:

34:57.750 --> 34:58.917
"HOPE DIES LAST."

34:58.917 --> 35:03.542
I ALWAYS LOVED IT.

35:05.375 --> 35:07.125
I THINK YOU'RE WAITING
FOR A SIGN.

35:07.125 --> 35:09.417
I'VE BEEN WAITING.

35:09.417 --> 35:11.417
I'M FREEZING
MY ASS OFF OUT HERE.

35:11.417 --> 35:13.792
DID IT EVER OCCUR
TO YOU, DAWSON LEERY,

35:13.792 --> 35:16.291
THAT MAYBE I'M THE SIGN
YOU'RE WAITING FOR?

35:26.000 --> 35:29.000
IT'S GONNA BE OK...

35:29.000 --> 35:31.792
FOR ALL OF US.

35:56.959 --> 35:57.959
YOU ALONE?

35:57.959 --> 36:00.333
NO. I GOT
THE VIENNA BOYS CHOIR WITH ME.

36:00.333 --> 36:02.041
[SIGHS]

36:02.041 --> 36:03.458
CAN WE PUT THE BITING
SARCASM TO REST?

36:05.792 --> 36:07.625
YOU WAITING FOR A BUS?

36:07.625 --> 36:09.125
NOPE. I'M JUST

36:09.125 --> 36:10.458
SITTING HERE
BEING COLD.

36:15.917 --> 36:17.667
[SIGHS]

36:20.041 --> 36:22.458
WHAT'S HAPPENED
TO YOU?

36:25.667 --> 36:27.458
OH, IT'S HARD TO SAY.

36:27.458 --> 36:30.542
I SEEM TO REMEMBER
THE TWO OF US

36:30.542 --> 36:32.333
HANGING OUT IN FRONT
OF THAT COFFEE STAND

36:32.333 --> 36:34.333
AT THE BEGINNING
OF THE YEAR.

36:34.333 --> 36:36.333
THEN "DUMB GUY
WITH A DREAM" COMES UP

36:36.333 --> 36:38.875
AND INVITES US
TO A FRATERNITY PARTY.

36:40.542 --> 36:43.250
EVERYTHING AFTER THAT'S
KIND OF A BLUR.

36:44.333 --> 36:46.083
JEN, CAN I ASK YOU
A QUESTION?

36:46.083 --> 36:49.000
YOU CAN ASK ME
A QUESTION.

36:50.166 --> 36:51.875
DID YOU LIKE
NOTTING HILL?

36:51.875 --> 36:54.834
ARE YOU KIDDING?
I LOVE THAT MOVIE.

36:54.834 --> 36:55.959
[SIGHS]

36:55.959 --> 36:58.083
[LAUGHS]

37:08.083 --> 37:10.542
YOU'RE RIGHT.
THE ENDING SUCKS.

37:12.625 --> 37:14.542
AUDREY.
HEY.

37:14.542 --> 37:15.625
ALL RIGHT.
OK.

37:15.625 --> 37:17.208
HERE'S WHAT
WE'RE GONNA DO.

37:17.208 --> 37:19.625
WE'RE GONNA
CUT ALL THIS.

37:19.625 --> 37:21.000
WE'RE JUST NOT
GONNA DO IT, OK?

37:21.000 --> 37:22.542
WE'RE GONNA KEEP THIS,
WE'RE GONNA KEEP THAT,

37:22.542 --> 37:25.208
AND WE'RE GONNA FORGET
ALL ABOUT THIS.

37:25.208 --> 37:27.041
AND WE'RE GONNA
END IT WITH THAT.

37:27.041 --> 37:28.417
NOW WHEN YOU DO IT,

37:28.417 --> 37:30.458
FORGET EVERYTHING
YOU'VE DONE UP UNTIL THIS POINT.

37:30.458 --> 37:32.750
THIS IS THE MOMENT WHERE
SHE LETS DOWN HER DEFENSES.

37:32.750 --> 37:34.875
IT'S NOT DRY,
IT'S NOT SARDONIC,

37:34.875 --> 37:37.250
IT'S JUST HONEST
AND IT'S VULNERABLE.

37:37.250 --> 37:39.458
NOW, WHEN YOU DO IT...

37:39.458 --> 37:40.500
[WHISPERING]

37:40.500 --> 37:43.792
BUT DOESN'T
THAT COMPLETELY--

37:43.792 --> 37:45.917
SHOOT FIRST,
ASK QUESTIONS LATER.

37:45.917 --> 37:47.208
OK.

37:47.208 --> 37:49.375
FRANK, YOU READY?

37:49.375 --> 37:50.250
OK.
OK.

37:50.250 --> 37:51.417
WE'RE GONNA DO THIS.

37:51.417 --> 37:53.959
AND WE'RE GONNA DO IT
IN ONE SHOT.

37:53.959 --> 37:55.417
THINK ORSON WELLES,
TOUCH OF EVIL.

37:55.417 --> 37:57.000
EVERYBODY KNOWS
WHERE THEY ARE.

37:57.000 --> 37:59.500
EVERYBODY KNOWS EXACTLY
WHAT THEY HAVE TO DO.

37:59.500 --> 38:01.542
LET'S BE THE BALL, PEOPLE.

38:01.542 --> 38:03.166
PICTURE'S UP.

38:05.750 --> 38:07.917
[LAUGHS]

38:07.917 --> 38:08.667
ROLLING.

38:08.667 --> 38:11.375
SCENE 32,
TAKE 1.

38:13.291 --> 38:15.125
[DAWSON LAUGHING]

38:15.125 --> 38:16.083
WHAT?

38:16.083 --> 38:18.542
AND...ACTION!

38:26.458 --> 38:28.000
YOU RUINED MY LIFE.

38:28.000 --> 38:30.834
YOU WRECKED ME!

38:32.792 --> 38:33.583
I KNOW...

38:35.834 --> 38:37.708
AND I'M SORRY.

38:40.500 --> 38:42.708
I DID A BAD THING.

38:46.250 --> 38:49.250
I'VE DONE A LOT
OF BAD THINGS
IN MY LIFE.

38:49.250 --> 38:52.792
I DIDN'T HAVE
A CHOICE.

38:52.792 --> 38:54.792
I HAD TO DO IT,

38:54.792 --> 38:56.917
BECAUSE IT WAS ALL
PART OF THE TRIP.

38:58.959 --> 39:00.542
Audrey: THE JOURNEY...

39:04.291 --> 39:06.000
TO THIS PLACE,

39:06.000 --> 39:08.583
THIS MOMENT,

39:08.583 --> 39:10.333
WITH YOU.

39:10.333 --> 39:12.166
THE THING
ABOUT LIFE?

39:12.166 --> 39:14.458
YOU CAN'T LOSE

39:14.458 --> 39:15.583
AND YOU CAN'T WIN...

39:17.333 --> 39:20.542
BUT YOU'VE GOT TO TRY.

39:22.375 --> 39:23.250
HOW DO YOU--
DON'T SPEAK.

39:23.250 --> 39:26.625
BUT--
DON'T SPEAK.

39:28.875 --> 39:30.458
[LAUGHS]

40:02.875 --> 40:03.667
FADE OUT.

40:15.083 --> 40:16.542
SO, LISTEN, I THINK I SHOULD
PROBABLY APOLOGIZE

40:16.542 --> 40:20.083
FOR WHAT HAPPENED EARLIER
UP IN YOUR ROOM.

40:20.083 --> 40:23.750
